 history are also included. An introduction to Quanzhen Daoism begins the work, and each chapter provides discussions of the history and topics relevant to each translation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aQuan zhen jiao. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Religion and Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Taoism. 7aRELIGION / Taoism (see also PHILOSOPHY / Taoist).2bisacsh1 aKomjathy, Louis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKomjathy, Louis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438446530423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438446530/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles